reviews: Clean comfortable hotel, friendly staff, nice restaurant, good service. Centrally located (close to the Louve) Easy to get a taxis and good restaurants close by. Very good staff, and service people. Thanks for a wonderful stay.

Amazing customer service, the hotel is doing a fabulous job at keeping staff happy and it showed!!! The amazing service started from the time I reached out by email to book this hotel with Eve and Melanie. They could not be more helpful in answering my questions and replying very quickly.

We booked a family/connecting rooms that consisted of a single door that opened to a small hallway where we had room 211-212. Very private and the kids loved having their own room. We could prop the door open so we could still hear them but had total privacy as well. I was nervous about the superior rooms being too small after reading some reviews, however they were bigger than expected and gorgeous! Our room had windows that looked on to the courtyard where I had fun seeing people take photo ops for their "emily in paris" imitation. Rooms were extremely clean, beds/linens/pillows were so comfortable we all had the best sleeps!

The concierge were very helpful, standout being the service I received from Germain...he went above and beyond and was not bothered by my requests for dinner and indecisiveness. Restaurant recommendations were great, and he also booked us skip the line tickets for the Arc which was very helpful. I also appreciated Suzanne the manager reaching out wanting my feedback directly and we would communicate by messenger. You could tell everyone cared about making your trip and stay the best it could possibly be.

Breakfast was included in the rate, overall good choices but my only recommendation would be to add perhaps pancakes, fresh berries and bran cereal but really it was quiet, unrushed and great service in the restaurant.

Location was amazing and although close to the Louvre we found the hotel situated in a quiet sanctuary away from the hustle and buzz of the crowds. I would not hesitate to stay here again and would recommend to anyone!

Great stay- very professional staff. We were greeting with champagne glasses and had a wine bottle as a welcoming gift in our room.
Room was beautiful- comfortable bed. Breakfast buffet was scrumptious and we also dined one evening at the hotel restaurant and the food was equally amazing. We used birthday cake package as well as a picnic in the park package and both were wonderful. Just an amazing stay. You can see Louvre from the window of facing the street side.

we stayed at the Grand Hotel du Palais Royal from May 5-12, 2023. The first 3 nights we had the rooftop suite and then moved to a regular room. The Rooftop suite was amazing. We have travelled with another couple and we have friends who live in Paris. So, the first three nights, we enjoyed the rooftop eating food we purchased from the local market and drinking wine.

We had a great view of the city from the roof and enjoyed the Eiffel Tower lighting up each night. This is very much a boutique hotel. It's small with not that many guests. Breakfast was included in our room rate and their breakfast each morning was outstanding. You could order eggs from the kitchen and also enjoy breads, fruits, cereals and cheeses from the buffet.

I can not say enough about the concierge staff. They were simply the best I have ever been around. They all spoke perfect english and were very willing and happy to provide assistance anytime we needed it. While moving from the rooftop suite to a regular room wasn't that great, that's out own fault for not booking far enough in advance to get the rooftop the entire time.

The hotel is very close to the Louvre and also to other hot spots. It's a little too far to walk to the Eiffel Tower but it's doable. One day we walked from the hotel to the Arc de Triumph and back without any issue. Our friends live in 4 and it was a quick metro ride over to see them.

We did day trips to Normandy and to Champagne - both were outstanding.

I would recommend this hotel to anyone.

Our travel agent selected this hotel for us based on our itinerary in Paris and it was perfect. One block from the Louvre, excellent shopping and restaurants within steps, and kind service. The rooms were nicely sized and bathrooms handy. Breakfast was included and was tasty, but weekday morning staff was a bit dour. Overall, great experience.

From the moment we checked in everyone at the hotel was so accommodating! This was my daughter’s and my first trip to Paris and this hotel was perfect!! The location, the comfort of our bedroom (we did have a jr balcony suite), the breakfast, the bar, the concierge…all top notch!!! We will be back!!

One of the best hotels that we have stayed at in Paris. This boutique hotel is exemplary in terms of location and service. It is located right across from the Palais Royal-Lourve metro which makes for easy transport around Paris. The staff, even before our stay, were so accommodating and helped us with our restaurant reservations. They are very attentive and are committed to provide the very best in customer service. If you need anything, they are there for you. They are very personalized and greet you by your name, everyday! The breakfast buffet food (which includes one made to order dish) was excellent, fresh and delicious. The made to order omelets were superb! Our room was an executive room, and it was spacious. My only complaint was that the room décor needs updating as there was a soiled spot on the bed headrest and chips and nicks in the furniture and doors. However, the room was very clean and the daily house cleaning service (twice a day) was efficient and thoughtful. They supply mineral water in cans twice a day. There is construction going on at the hotel with scaffolding around the exterior and some of the rooms look to be under remodel in preparation for the 2024 Olympics. But the noise was not a problem. We would not hesitate to stay at the Grand Hotel du Palais Royal again and highly recommend it.

Very welcoming service from all of the staff, from the front desk to the concierge to the breakfast and room service staff, excellent room for the price, very conveniently located for the Louvre and Musee d'Orsay,

This is an excellent hotel with all amenities including tour and driver assistance. The location is excellent as It is right across the street from the Louvre. They provided a private tour guide for the Louvre as well.

Comfortable, quiet, clean rooms. Exceptional staff and service. Breakfast is fantastic.
Terrific location in the Right Bank. We didn't care for dinner options in Cafe 52 but there are lots of cafes nearby. Highly recommend GHdPR!

We stayed at the Grand Hotel Du Palais Royal for an entire week and we were thrilled with the beautiful hotel, excellent service and wonderful staff.

The rooms were clean, well appointed and comfortable. Room service was delicious and delivered with a sincere smile…even at 6:00 am! 😊

The location was perfect. Walking distance from the Louvre. Our concierge, Germain, got tickets for us and we spent an entire day enjoying the museum.

The hotel is surrounded by charming cafes, restaurants, coffee shops and cute boutiques. All within walking distance.

The staff understood our needs and desires and went out of their way to take care of us. We were greeted by name and they were always interested in hearing about our day.

We stayed over the Easter holiday and they hid chocolate eggs in our room while we were out enjoying the city. That was a special touch!

A member of our party got sick and the concierge arranged a doctor’s visit to her room. The doctor was fluent in English and had an excellent bedside manner.

If we ever return to Paris…we will definitely stay at the Palais Royal again. Happily.

We had a chance to enjoy a brand new suite "Emily" that was beautiful, stylish and so silent ! A miracle in the heart of Paris. What I appreciate the most, is definitely the staff, from the restaurant to the concierge, everybody worked to make our stay memorable. Thank you !

the staff was one of the most accommodative staff's we have ever worked with. from arranging our daily travel plans to helping with meals and logistics, they were able to provide 100% perfection every time.

I can't rave enough about this hotel. The location is excellent, the room is so comfortable and beautifully appointed and the service is impeccable. Anytime I made a request it was met within minutes. The staff is friendly and accommodating from the front desk to the restaurant to the room make-up. Breakfast was included in my stay and they have a great buffet. Rooms are on the small side but I had one with a balcony which I so enjoyed. I can't wait to go back!

Overall an excellent stay. The staff was extremely polite & welcoming. The concierge was helpful and welcoming. The hotel itself is beautiful and in a perfect location. The rooms weren't spectacular, but after a long day of eating 4,000 croissants, my wife and I slept great.

Excellent staff all around; welcoming and helpful. Happy to assist in any way possible. They want to help you have a great time in Paris.

We were given the ability to shower up and change upon arrival since we were early and check in was not available. Also offered champagne, coffee and tea. All welcome after a long day of travel.

Breakfast was good no matter if you had it served in your room or went to the buffet downstairs.

Room was quiet and very comfortable. If you want a hot shower, do it in the morning, when the hot water is ample.

Would 100% stay again and recommend to friends and family.

Perfectly located in the heart of Paris, the hotel is elegant with comfortable rooms and off the noisy main streets. Being small and cozy makes you feel right at home. A nice treat is that the Louvre Museum is only a few steps away.

The hotel was rather a perfect location. The staff are exceptional on every level. I just love the smell, the atmosphere, the location. The pillows, the bedding, the bathroom, the view ... just love it.

Welcoming, all of staffs were very kind, front desk, concierge were very supportive when I was booking my tickets. They helped me all the way and even gave me recommendation what time I should leave to go to the station. Additionally, when I checked out, they showed me off to the taxi and guided me to show the palace royal garden which was right in front of the hotel, it was very nice place to take a stroll. Location was perfect, interior was nice.

P.S: Please advise the company who supply shaving kit, cap of razor blade were off when I tried to open it and I got cut. Other than that, everything was very great!

I had come to stay in this hotel in July 2022, at the end of July I had taken the time to write a comment on this hotel on Trip Advisor, in fact I had put a bad note because for a hotel of this standard and at this price , we expected to have a larger room, following the writing of my comment, I had even received an email from the management and indeed I had not replied. If my comment is still deleted then I would no longer have confidence in Trip Advisor, this will mean that from now on it is no longer possible to really say what we think, it is a beautiful hotel but charging prices that are really too high compared to what we had received,

All staff were amazing and I would highly recommend this hotel - best in Paris!
We went to celebrate my daughters 18th birthday and nothing was too much trouble from the reception staff to the concierge and waitress.
This hotel is a must if you are visiting Paris.

But she didn’t see the bill.
We had a perfectly fine deluxe double-room on the second floor. I had asked for something on an upper floor, months in advance and again a week before our arrival but, oh well, not a big deal. I had also asked for a quiet room. We were facing the Place de Valois which normally would be ideal. Unfortunately, there is construction going on there so in addition to the ugly scaffolding there is constant noise during work hours. It’s true, most guests are not in their rooms during those hours but...still. There is also a big renovation of the Louvre des Antiquaires so that means disruptions on the rue Saint-Honoré and a big, glass-clad, temporary (?) structure blocking half the Place du Palais-Royal. Add that to the fact that this area is one of the big tourist nodes of the city and it makes for a less than ideal location right now, in my opinion. Rooms are priced to keep out the riff-raff. I guess that’s important to some people. (Definitely a very good breakfast, though)

My husband and I visited in April. This hotel was fantastic. The location was amazing and easily accessible. The hotel was modern and clean. Our room was a good size and housekeeping did a great job keeping things clean. One thing that my husband and I continue to reminisce about is the concierge services. We reached out well in advance of our stay to get their assistance with booking dinner reservations. They had plenty of recommendations and they were able to book everything in advance. Once we were on property, we dealt mainly with Gerald. He really made our visit to Paris something special. A concierge can make or break a visit to a new city or hotel - and Gerald really left a positive impression on us. He really went above and beyond to make our stay easy and comfortable. We plan on staying here again when we return to Paris. Highly recommend!!

Excellent Hotel. The service was top-notch. We have stayed at many brand-new high-end hotels recently in Paris and this one was by far the best from a service perspective. Speedy check-in, all the details of our special requests included, excellent.

Everyone at the hotel was warm, attentive and dedicated to assisting with our stay. Our room had a nice corner view of the Palais Royal and was very quiet at night. Our concierge Germain went above and beyond to get us reservations at a top tier restaurant. We had the most romantic two days in celebration of our anniversary.

We bookended a river cruise with pre and post cruise nights at this hotel. The hotel is a boutique hotel and a member of the small luxury hotels of the world
The staff is efficient pleasant and courteous. They speak English and are also quite helpful for answering questions or making reservations for dining. I wax impressed with everyone I came onto contact with from the staff.
The location cannot be beat if staying in the 1st AR is your wish. The royal palace gardens are directly across the street and both louvre and opera are within an easy walk. You have shopping and dining options on both Rue Rivoli and Rue St. Honore also within an easy walk.

Fabulous property, amazing location for all the right reasons. Top notch staff only adds to the wonderfulness of this property. First the location. Not are you central to just about everything in Paris including the Metro, but the immediate area surrounding the property is quaint, quiet and makes you feel like you live in Paris. Every day, we enjoyed the Palais Royal which is right across the street.

The hotel staff do an amazing job providing 5 Star service at all levels, with personal attention and maintaining every aspect of the property. The fact that the hotel is small means you'll be on a first name basis with the staff. Whatever you need, they are there to help.

Food selection around the hotel is excellent, but their own restaurant, Cafe 52 is amazing, especially if you want a break from the plethora of bistrot options.

This hotel is definitely deserving of membership to the Small Luxury Hotel (SLH) group. Highly recommend and would have a hard time not staying here during our next Paris visit.

We really enjoyed this hotel. The location is wonderful! Staff was accommodating. I’d recommend upgrading your room as we did. I felt safe. The metro is close by. The Louvre is next door. There are lots of excellent cafes and bistros and shops nearby. Small, yet clean, spa and gym. We used the steam room and showered only to learn that there were folks of opposite sex also using the same area. It’s all one.breakfast was excellent. Very expensive and very nice.

Staff was excellent. Location is wonderful! The staff was accommodating and spoke English very well. Our housekeeper was fabulous! Next door to the Louvre. There’s a train station on the next block. We felt (and were) safe. Nice small gym and clean spa downstairs. The location is worth it! Lots of wonderful cafes nearby, it’s high end and you pay for what you get. I felt the Royal Palais hotel was “expensive” overall compared to other hotels though we upgraded our room after arrival as I wanted more from the general view they’d offered us at first …so we paid more for a better view. If I had to do t again, I’d opt for their best room. Heck—if you pay $650 per night it should be “tres grande.” And it was. I recommend this hotel and would stay there again. The breakfasts were delicious. The bar was quaint. It was fun! My 6th visit to France. And the hotel was great!

The Grand Hôtel du Palais Royal is a beautiful hotel in a great location. The rooms are comfortable, the bar and restaurant are comfortable and quiet, and the staff is helpful and friendly. Both times I stayed at the hotel, the concierge arranged tours for me and they were always fantastic. Finally, the hotel is walking distance to many of the great museums and theaters in Paris.

I loved our stay at the Grand Hotel du Palais Royal - we stayed here for 4 nights and wish we could have stayed longer. Tucked into a small street right next to the Domaine National du Palais Royal, this hotel is a lovely, luxurious retreat from the bustle of Paris. I found our room (a deluxe room) to be well sized for a Parisian and the décor is just the right balance of luxury and opulence. It was incredibly convenient to anywhere we want to go - step outside the hotel and you're right in the courtyard of the Domaine National du Palais Royal or walk just 1 minute and you're at the Louvre. At the corner is the Metro so you're never far from anywhere you need to go.

What elevates this hotel above and beyond others, however, is the staff! The concierge and staff were warm, helpful and friendly. When we arrived too early to check in, staff offered us access to the spa downstairs to freshen up - a small gesture that means so much to the weary traveler. The turn down service was twice daily, discrete, and such a lovely thing to come home to - indeed, it began to feel like home after the first two days and I wish we didn't have to leave. I hope to be lucky enough to come back and stay here again.

You're steps from the Seine. You're also in your own private alcove snuck between the Palais Royal and the Pont des Arts. It's intimate and quiet. Perfect location and the staff are all fantastic and friendly too!

Privileged to travel often in retirement to favourites of my work career, I came to know the Grand Hotel du Palais Royal as deserving of its highest accolades, and following the posting of a review focused on a disappointing stay in May of this year, I have taken that review down, and have been assured that the COVID-19 related deficiencies – the impossibility of hiring knowledgeable and competent help, etc. -- which I had pointed out shall have been soon addressed: a major renovation, half the building at a time, is ongoing, with an eye toward re-achieving the perfection we once knew, both inside the edifice and in the adjacent outdoor patio. I am assured there shall be no disappointments of the sort my wife and I encountered. Given the many outstanding experiences we have had there, I trust that the management shall again achieve the deserved five-star rating.

This hotel was absolutely amazing. They treated us so well. They were so sweet and pleasant. The hotel was clean and pristine. It’s around the corner from the louvre. 2 mins walking. The area is so beautiful and classic Parisian. I’m def staying here when I go back.

Our hotel stay was quite wonderful. The room was comfortable and clean. The bath after a long day walking through the city was greatly appreciated. Breakfast was the same daily—a cold buffet with your choice of eggs. Pancakes, French toast, etc was at an additional cost. We used the laundry service without problem but it is expensive. I think it was $5 to wash a pair of socks.

From check-in to concierge to service we were treated like family not guests . First time in Paris and needed a lot of advice and guidance . With cab strike , Thomas the concierge offered to use his personal Uber account to get us around . Great room ; great staff ; great stay .

This hotel is truly a lovely, stylish, boutique hotel located in the center of Paris but in a quiet alcove in the palais royale buildings. It is walking distance to most parts of Paris. The staff is very personable and helpful. The breakfasts were excellent and the service was too. We also had dinner there one night after a full day of sightseeing and the menu and food were delicious!

We stayed here for 4 nights and had the most amazing time. The room was beyond expectations and the staff was more than attentive. It was so nice to get little check ins from the team making sure our visit was going well and we had what we needed. We loved that the hotel was nestled a block off from a main road, yet close enough to the Metro and walkable to almost everything we did. We've already made plans to visit Paris again next fall and will most assuredly be staying here again. Thank you all for a memorable visit!

The hotel was perfect. The service - from the time we arrived - to the moment was left was superb. Everyone was very professional, friendly, and most helpful. The room was quiet and dark which made sleeping an average of 10 hours each night quite easy.

Gorgeous boutique hotel in a prime location. You’ll be in walking distance to all the sights and luxury shopping destinations. Friendly staff and great service. The bathroom was spacious and well appointed. The terrace was tiny, could not sit comfortably in the space to really enjoy the view. Overall, very pleased with the accommodations. Everything was as expected for a 5-star hotel in Paris.

Wonderful boutique hotel in a great location near the Louvre. Staff is friendly and helpful, concierge did a fantastic job booking our meals and excursions. Our room included breakfast which offered plenty of great options from yogurt to pastries to omelets.
My wife and I highly recommend.

My wife and I came here to celebrate our 40th wedding anniversary. Our suite with balcony was very nice.

Reception staff are really friendly and helpful and we were welcomed with a glass of champagne which was a nice touch

The bar staff make a fantastic Cosmopolitan

Yes 5 stars to this gorgeous little hidden gem next to the palace and literally a view away from the Louvre. We were fortunate to stay on the 5th floor in a suite with not one but two balconies with views of Sacre Cour, the palace and Louvre! Wonderful service by all from start to finish. The included breakfast (which you can have in room as well) was incredible and so many choices! Very fresh and delicious. Our bath was noteworthy large for France standards with a tub and separate shower. Would highly recommend this hotel for a great location and excellent service and well earned Small Luxury Hotel. Merci!

So charming and quaint....wonderful staff and intimate lobby with beautiful courtyard in back. (where emily in paris is filmed....so panoramic and stunning.) My daughter and I loved being a stone's throw from the Louvre and the beautiful toulliere gardens and so many cafes and restaurants.

We would rate it 100 if we could. From the beginning of the stay to the end, the staff were attentive and professional. They couldn’t do enough to make our stay comfortable and special. The rooms were clean and comfortable, the toiletries wonderful and the hotel decor was very chic without being over the top - exactly what we were after. The location unbeatable. The whole stay was an exercise in how the hospitality industry should be as standard. Our thanks to the whole team for making it a memorable 10 year wedding anniversary

A convenient gem of a hotel !
My teenage daughter and I stayed at this hotel for 8 nights at the end of July/beginning of August. You cannot beat the location in terms of convenience, safety, ease. The concierge staff is first rate. They were able to secure reservations at every spot we requested. They arranged a private guide and transportation to Versailles that was wonderful. They also arranged shipping via DHL of flea market purchases back to the us. Truly the staff made our stay much easier for me !
Our room faced the Valois courtyard and was very quiet. While small, it was clean and the bathroom was modern and efficient. Breakfast was included in our room rate and it was more than adequate. Friendly staff and delicious breakfast. I would defiantly stay there again. Palais royale is across the street and a beautiful stroll in the early am !

My husband and I just got back from our nine night stay at the Grand Hotel du Palais Royal. I wanted to offer them my compliments on our entire stay.
We arrived on July 12th as our train from London was delayed and we were pressed for time and the road to your hotel was closed due to construction. Concierge member Irina and another one of her coworkers were the first smiles we saw as our cab was parked by the Cafe Royal. She came down the street to help get our luggage out of the car, take it back to the hotel and check us in so we could get to a food tour in Le Marais. WOW!!!! So we were so impressed from checkin to check out by your entire staff.

Every time we came in from being out all day, we were greeted by smiles and a BONJOUR which felt like being home. The concierge team and especially Irina, are EXCEPTIONAL! They are knowledgable and friendly and helpful. Every single reservation they made for us was PERFECT. Every change they did for me was also PERFECT. The bar area is beautiful and relaxing, the drinks are cool and refreshing. The dining area was comfortable and peaceful and the food was delicious.

The front desk staff are friendly helpful and also delightful. One girl at the front desk even came out and spoke to the cab driver to make sure we got to where we needed to go.

The room was small, BUT had everything we needed. The bed and pillows were comfortable and the balcony was what I wanted. I loved having room service in the room and the Nespresso coffee maker as well. When we ordered room service it came on time and efficiently. ALWAYS with a smile.

I cant say enough wonderful things about this hotel. The location is perfect, the staff is professional and caring and the facilities we welcoming.

Thank you for all you ALL do for us as guests. We will be back.

We enjoyed our stay at this hotel! After a long international flight, we were able to freshen up in their spa. They also held our bags, so we could grab lunch before check-in. We stayed in another Paris hotel later in our trip. The rooms at The Grand Hotel du Palais Royal were large in comparison! The rooms were also clean, quiet and conveniently located near the Louvre. We would definitely stay here again!

We absolutely loved this hotel. The room design is efficient with beautiful decor, the customer service is excellent and there are thoughtful touches. The bathroom mirror is anti fog, there are small tables to enjoy the balcony and the toiletries provided are diptyque brand which smells amazing. Outlets are accessible and we even discovered champagne delivered to our room one day!

The staff are welcoming and helpful and efficient. The rooms are comfortable and the bathrooms are lovely. The restaurant is very good for both breakfast and cocktails. This hotel gets consistent high marks because they earn every star every day. Such a lovely experience in a terrific location steps from metro, Louvre, Tulleries, and Laduree!

This hotel knows how to treat their customers , also their rooms are a good size for Paris and everything in the room was perfect . We had a room with a balcony and we were surprised at the size of it . The restaurant had a good breakfast with very good service . The location was great just a few minutes from the Louvre by foot . You can't go wrong with this hotel and we hope to return soon . Thank you Grand Hotel du Palais Royal .

The staff went above and beyond to make sure that our stay was as comfortable and amazing as possible. They constantly checked in with us to see if our needs were being met and to assist with any questions/concerns we had. The room was gorgeous and very comfortable. Breakfast was delicious every morning with great service. We would absolutely stay here again.

This hotel is off a quiet street in a wonderful neighborhood, within a few minutes walk to so many great things to see and foods to eat. The hotel staff is attentive, the quality and cleanliness was very good, and everything was quite comfortable.

Great for everything, location, service, facilities, breakfast and others.
Will recommend if you are visitors for paris with schedules near the Louvre and shopping near Vandom and Samaritanne.
Hope to stay again for next visit

The location is close to all and walking distance to the Louvre. Most of all what makes this hotel great is the staff. They are all so attentive to the needs of the guests. I stayed here with my teenage daughter and she did not want to leave the hotel even to go shopping. We will be staying here on our next visit and recommended it to my family and friends.

My wife and I traveled to Paris for our honeymoon, and we are very pleased with our decision to stay at the Grand Hotel du Palais Royal. From the moment we arrived at the hotel on Tuesday afternoon until the moment we departed on Saturday, the service we received was consistently first class and made us feel completely at home. Suzanne, the guest experience manager, checked in with us periodically to ensure that our stay was comfortable, and Alexandre and the concierge staff graciously assisted us with making restaurant reservations and booking sightseeing attractions like the Seine River cruise. We could not have asked for a better experience, and we will definitely be staying at the Grand Hotel du Palais Royal the next time we are in Paris!

It is the second time we have chosen to stay at the Palais Royal for a week-end in Paris.

The Palais Royal is a palais in its true sense: The reception is warm and attentive, the rooms are splendid and the ingredients for breakfast carefully selected. When sitting in the breakfast room with a view on the Place de Valois, you might even catch a look at the film set of 'Emily in Paris'!

We thoroughly enjoyed our stay here. The hotel is in a great location in the 1st. The staff was incredibly warm and inviting. We stayed in an executive room, and though it was small, it was well appointed and extremely comfortable to sleep in. Highly recommend!

Not much to find fault with here. Yeah the rooms were a little small but the positives far outweigh the negatives. The location was nice just a short walk from the Louvre and there are numerous places to eat within five minutes. Breakfast at the hotel was very good and fast. The staff at the front desk and concierge were both very helpful. They provided us with some excellent recommendations for meals and gave good advice on how to get around.

Our first visit to Paris as our Honeymoon and could not fault the staff or accommodation.

The team were friendly and very helpful.

On arrival we were offered either water or champagne at check in which was a nice touch.

Location is great, central and nice district with great bars and brassiere near by with 10 minute walk.

My wife and I stayed for our 20th wedding anniversary and were treated like royalty when we arrived. The service during our stays was top notch and really helped make our trip a memorable one. We highly recommend this hotel and would love to visit again.

Our trip from the US to Paris had been years in the making as we came to see the Adam Lambert & Queen concert in Paris that had originally been scheduled for 2020 which, due to COVID, finally happened in 2022. The location of this hotel is ideal....the center of everything. Our room was the amazing Suite Panoramique....at the top of the hotel with a terrace featuring perfect views Lourve, Eiffel Tower, Opera house and Sacré Coeur de Montmartre. That about covers it! The room itself is comfortable & functional but not opulent....which is perfect. The air conditioning was not up to the temperatures during our visit...but it was 90+F most days. Room service breakfast is amazing....French Toast to die for!!!. Room service in general is marginal. The in-Room Dining systems/processes are problematic. Never call In-Room Dining...they dont answer. Call the Reception and ask to be transferred...then it will keep ringing until they answer. Lunch & Dinner menu is limited and focused "healthy" choices. But sometimes, I would just love a turkey sandwich or something "normal". Not here. Staff is friendly. But not trainied to "World Class" standards. They are great until there is a problem...then they suddenly cant speak/understand English. :) But its all minor. I am fairly independent. I do not rely on the hotel to provide transportation or reservations. I do that myself. This is the way to be here...then you will be thrilled. We will be back and we will stay here (but will plan our lunches and dinners elsewhere...hey, its Paris. No issue there!).

I stayed here with my wife for 2 nights and had a fantastic time. The staff are phenomenal; attentive, good knowledge and always smiling. Rooms were well done and well kitted out and a good size (for Paris).

Tucked away an unassuming side street in the center of Paris, Grand Hotel du Palais Royal is a hidden jewel perfect for tourists & business people alike. Clean rooms, friendly staff, & fantastic food at Cafe 52.

The service is excellent as is the location. The wellness area is a luxury and sets this hotel apart. They have a large steam sauna with showers, robes, etc., which were easily accessible and which we used several times during our stay. Being right across the street from the Louvre is convenient. The only downsides are that the rooms are small for a five-star hotel (it is Paris, after all) and thus the beds are small (full). I would stay here again. Very happy with my stay here.

From the moment I arrived at this beautiful place, I was greeted with a happy expediency. The staff was extremely attentive offering a glass of champagne and offering to take pictures as I checked in. I received immediate help with my luggage and my room was ready prior to check in. I was offered a tour of the hotel and informed about the amenities. Each and every time I called the concierge, it was a success! Every question I had answered. The rooms were impeccably clean with beautiful views. There water and a bottle of wine upon arrival. The beds and pillows were so comfortable and dream inducing. I enjoyed restful sleep each time. Breakfast was lovely and the staff welcoming and efficient. I will definitely stay here again!

We stayed at this hotel on the back end of a seven day trip. We wished we would have stayed there the entire time. It was an incredible location, the staff was bilingual and exceptional, and the room was large and had plenty of space. We stayed on the 6th floor in one of the large rooms but it was well worth the additional money. It was our 10th wedding anniversary and they had a bottle of champagne waiting on us in the room which was a nice touch. The concierge was spot on and helped us with just about everything include covid testing, car service, and restaurants.

The location was unbeatable as was the service. Friendly staff, who were always available and smiling. Having stayed at European hotels across the world, I know what to expect when it comes to size of the rooms but having booked a Deluxe Room. I must say I was disappointed with the postage stamp size room we got. There wasn’t even space for the coffee machine which had to take up real estate on the dressing table. Tried bringing this up with the front desk but the hotel was full and probably nothing they could do anyways. Manage your expectations on room size and you will not be disappointed with the rest of your experience.

Our room was beautiful and the bathroom and amenities were great. The staff was helpful and kind. The breakfast each day was delicious and fresh. We will return. The proximity to the metro and all of the main attractions was perfect for us.

This is my absolute favorite hotel in Paris. Perfect location, helpful staff, great rooms, bar and breakfast. Everything is amazing here - great for traveling alone, as a couple or group/family. Perfection overall!

Room was small, but comfortable, with a big bathroom!
The "balcony" was in name only.
Free breakfast was a nice bonus.
Concierge was extremely helpful.
Location was just perfect, literally next door to the Louvre!!

I cannot say enough about the helpful and friendly staff. Every single need met and exceeded expectations. The rooms are a little small but that is to be expected in Europe. Even though they were small, they still met our every need and our stay was comfortable and amazing.

We stayed at the hotel for 4 days and the service was excellent. All staff were very accommodating and helped with any enquiry we had, recommending some great restaurants (L’absinthe and Pain, Vin et Fromage). Jussi was very kind and extremely helpful.

We used the pool, sauna and steam room. All a lovely addition to our relaxing stay.

Would highly recommend!

Excellent value. Quick checkin, quiet area. Comfortable rooms. Many classic nearby eating places. Staff responsive and helpful. Pleasant view overlooking courtyard. Very comfortable beds and pillows. Highly recommend.

We recently spent 6 nights in a Junior Suite room with two balconies (Chambre 507). This hotel is everything you could ask for in a hotel in Paris. It has location, spacious rooms and bathrooms, and above all, the best service and most gracious employees. We have stayed at three hotels and one VRBO in Paris, and this hotel competes with the best--Le Meurice, Peninsula, Westin Tuileries. Actually, the service was superior to all but Le Meurice, which it equaled. Upon check-in, we were upgraded to a Junior Suite with two balconies. The concierges were so friendly and helpful. Special compliments to Augustin, Thomas and Alexandre for all their help and warm courtesy. I cannot imagine not staying here next time I am in Paris. Well done to the Grand Hotel du Palais Royale! Je t'aime!

Great location and truly terrific and friendly service by the entire staff. The Concierges were outstanding!
One comment is that we moved to a higher level of rooms but the room was smaller (particularly the bathroom), and more expensive. Only benefit: a minuscule balcony

Just spent 5 nights at the hotel and loved it! Fantastic location on a quiet and very pretty street. We booked a Jr Suite but were upgraded to a suite. It was so comfortable and lovely. Comfortable beds and pillows and a fantastic bathroom! Shower fabulous which I always love. Lobby of the hotel charming. Restaurant/ breakfast room very chic and you can also sit outside in the beautiful plaza. Nice selection of foods and wonderful service. Bar also nice to have a coffee or drink. Staff just amazing, kind and helpful. Special shout out to their fantastic and helpful Concierge- Thomas. Just fabulous and every suggestion he gave us was great. I loved my stay and will definitely go back !

A very nice hotel in a quiet plaza two blocks from the Louvre within walking distance of major attractions and great restaurant districts . We stayed two nights on the 4th floor overlooking the courtyard. The staff were incredibly friendly and helpful and the room clean and comfortable.

We traveled to Paris for our 32nd wedding anniversary. We had never been to Paris, and had envisioned Paris as a romantic, enchanting city. From the time we decided to book this hotel, we started working with the concierge team of Thomas, and Gerald, who painstakingly researched and booked tours and skip the line sightseeing excursions for us. Every email to the team was met with timely responses, and great ideas. They also helped us to book a day trip to Brussels. We booked our transportation through the hotel as well, and the driver met us at airport baggage with a name placard.
It was a very smooth process, and we arrived at the hotel quickly. We were met outside by concierge staff, who took our luggage and walked us into the hotel.
We were offered champagne, a place to freshen up, and a tour of the hotel amenities. As we arrived early, our room was not yet ready. They held our luggage, and texted us when our room was available.
Thomas and Gerald went out of their way to assure that we had a great experience. Thomas gave us all of our excursion tickets along with a map of Paris and of the Metro. He explained everything to us and the best way to navigate Paris. He helped us with dinner reservations and listened to what we wanted.

The hotel itself is immaculate. The rooms are nicely appointed and there is turn down service. We received fresh towels twice daily. We had a balcony room which was beautiful, and the bathroom was spacious with a heated towel rack.
There is plenty of staff, and never a line to wait on.
Gerald helped us with daily information, and helped me learn French. He is so genuine, pleasant, and went beyond to make sure we had the best trip ever.
The breakfast offered by the hotel is delicious, and the wait staff is attentive and friendly.
I would definitely stay here again, and recommend this hotel highly. They are in the 1st arrondizment, close to the Louvre and the Seine, on the right bank.

Gerald was an amazing concierge and now a new friend! We loved everything about the hotel and will be back the next time we visit Paris.

Thank you for making our stay so comfortable and enjoyable. This hotel is THE BEST!

Everything was excellent. Great service and care to make sure that everything is perfect. Could babble aimlessly just to achieve two hundred characters bu I have always believed that brevity is a virtue and blather is to be avoided.

A Beautiful small hotel perfectly situated to explore all of Paris. The service was exceptional, and the concierge amazing at recommending restaurants, booking them and checking our stay was as it should be. A super friendly 5 star hotel, we will definitely go back.

Stayed at this fantastic hotel for my wife's birthday. This hotel is located right next the the Louvre and the river, you really can't get better. Lots of cafe bars/restaurants on streets around the hotel. We had the hotel transfer which was brilliant, right to the door and back to the hotel. a warm welcome when we arrived and show the room by the reception staff (nice touch) we booked a room with a balcony (see picture) which was nice to have. Only small point was room/bathroom was small but I guess being in the heart of Paris and your not in it much during the day was acceptable but worth noting. breakfast was tasty, traditional continental style.
Overall a great stay, wanted to stay longer and would recommend and stay here again.

Fabulous hotel with super friendly and helpful staff on reception and concierge who were always ready to assist and make suggestions. Very comfortable and spacious room - although minor point, no mirror near a power socket in the bedroom. Great location from which to get to all the sights - perfect!

We had a fantastic stay, the room was excellent, the staff were all very friendly and attentive. It’s location is perfect very close to the Louvre and lots of great restaurantsWould highly recommend this hotel.

We loved our week-long stay at the Grand Hotel du Palais Royal. Everything exceeded our expectations. The location was perfect for heading out to sight see each day. The staff went above and beyond and we especially loved Gerard and Tomas, two of the Concierges. They helped us secure restaurant reservations, concert and museum tickets, and helped with travel tips among other things. They were a wealth of knowledge. We would gladly stay here again.

Lovely place a block down from Louvre, so quiet and still close to everything Paris has to offer. The most friendly staff catering to anything we needed. We are so happy to have a place to call home away from home when our travel takes us to Paris

We loved the Grand Hotel du Palais Royal! This is our second trip to Paris and we won't stay anywhere else on future visits! We love luxury boutique hotels (small to mid size) and prefer them over the big Palace type hotels.

The staff is incredibly friendly. Gerald (concierge) is so helpful, attentive, knowledgeable, and kind. It is clear that he loves his job and is amazing at it. Thank you so much, Gerald! The front desk staff and Jonas in the bar were incredibly kind as well. Every staff member we encountered was friendly and helpful.

The breakfast in the hotel restaurant is wonderful and thank you to Jonas and Armand who were so kind and attentive. A great way to start your day!

The location is close to everything! We walked to the Louvre, the Seine, the Latin Quarter, the Marais, Notre Dame, to restaurants, the Opera House and shopping, etc. We took the Metro a few times and the stop is right by the hotel. Extremely convenient.

We booked our room through our travel agent (Virtuoso affiliated) and received a room upgrade to a Junior Suite with balcony. The room was a nice size (especially by European standards), very clean, very quiet, and the bathroom was nice sized with wonderful water pressure and consistent heated water.

If you are considering this hotel, book it! If you like luxury, boutique hotels with friendly and attentive service, you have found the perfect option!

What a glorious week we just spent at the Grand Hotel du Palais Royal! When planning a trip, the hotel is usually my top concern (admitted hotel snob!). As it was our first time in Paris (coming from US), I was overwhelmed by the many wonderful hotels to choose from. But I kept coming back to this one. Even before we arrived, I was in regular contact with the concierge department requesting recommendations and booking for excursions, meals, sights. Specifically Gerald was amazing, always responding very promptly with many choices and recs. From the moment we arrived, we were treated like longtime family. We had arranged car transport through the hotel and were picked up in a Mercedes, making the drive after the long transatlantic flight much more comfortable. Upon arrival, we were offered champagne and they held our bags as it was very early and the room not ready. They had all of our documents ready and organized for all the things we had booked. Upon returning later in the day, we were escorted to our room. They had so graciously upgraded us from a Deluxe to an Executive room. It was beautiful, with two floor length windows opening onto a double balcony overlooking a courtyard. A bottle of chilled champagne was waiting as a gift to celebrate our 20th anniversary. The courtyard may be recognizable if you're an Emily in Paris fan (which I had not seen prior to arrival and had no clue!). Throughout our weeklong stay, the staff was just perfection. They attended to all of our needs, greeted us by name each day and went out of their way to ensure we were beyond satisfied at every turn. Gerard and the other concierge staff members attended to last minute change of minds with dinners and secured others at a moment's notice. The hotel is decorated in a modern way with modern amenities while retaining the charm of the historic building and palace for which it is named. The location is perfect, right across from the Louvre and a few short blocks from the Seine and Musee d'Orsay. We absolutely cannot think of staying anywhere else when we return to Paris.

Great location close to the Louvre. Lots of shopping, bistros and restaurants close by. Much to my surprise there was even a J Town area close by. Hotel room is a bit small but clean and everything you need. Nice soaking tub. Only down sides was the renos to the restaurant but did not affect us as we did not eat in the hotel. Everyone on staff was very friendly and helpful. Would definitely return again.

We were so happy with the accommodations at the Palais Royal. The room was amazing and the views were spectacular. The staff were all very helpful and friendly which admittedly is not a given in Paris. They all also spoke english very well. We only ordered room service once and the food was spectacular. The concierge (Gerald) was ESPECIALLY great in helping us with everything and anything. It was like having a personal assistant! Thank you for a wonderful experience!

Me and my daughter have stayed in The Grand Hôtel Du Palais Royal twice now and we absolutely love it. The location is amazing (near the Louvre, the Rue de Rivoli, all the shops on the Rue St Honoré, the Metro, short walk over to the Tuileries Gardens or The Seine) and the staff are super helpful and assist in finding and booking restaurants, museums or printing out tickets. The breakfast room has an iconic Parisian courtyard view which is a brilliant start to the day.

Stayed 3 nights at The Grand Hotel du Palias Royal with my wife and son. The staff were fantastic and couldn't have done more. Alexandre and Gerald at the concierge desk we're brilliant in helping us find restaurants and book a visit to the Louvre. Location was just perfect, within walking distance of everything we wanted to see and our room was very comfortable and quiet. We'll definitely be back...

The hotel is well organized and perfectly located for those who want to be right in the middle of the touristic attractions. Even though the rooms are not as big as we expected, their services made it nice and complete. We would like to specially thank GERALD, who was from the very beginning very helpful and kind (all the rest were as well… but Gerald is truly a bonus).

Great location very walkable to all sites. Gerard the concierge was terrific. All staff very friendly and fluent in English. Rooms small like all european rooms tend to be.
Hotel is very nice for the price.

We thoroughly enjoyed our stay at Grand Hotel du Palais Royal. The staff was so attentive and friendly, the rooms were spacious and meticulously kept, and we really felt at home. Also, there's a terrific happy hour and a wonderful breakfast. Special kudos to Gerald who went above and beyond to find an item that my daughter left behind in her room.

Very comfortable hotel, nice rooms (rather small but typical of most Paris hotels) with caring and attentive staff. Terrific and very quiet location right in the centre of Paris but very close to the Metro.

The team members at the hotel were English fluent, service-oriented, helpful, solicitous, & fun! The concierges were the best I’ve experienced anywhere in the world! The hotel was lovely in a great section very convenient to the sights. My room was well appointed, clean & had a wonderful view! We’re planning a trip back next year.

We just returned from a wonderful stay at the Grand Hotel Du Palais Royal. The hotel is just beautiful and very clean. They have so many nice amenities, and the staff could not have been nicer or more helpful. The restaurant is beautiful and has a terrific breakfast and bar. We loved the staff at the restaurant and bar. Gerald, Thomas and the entire concierge staff make your trip so special. The location is perfect too as it’s both central, and yet quietly tucked away. We can’t wait to return!

Beautiful charming hotel, fantastic location, warm, welcoming, and helpful staff, excellent food at Cafe 52. The concierge service was so helpful both before and during our stay. It was an excellent experience and I will certainly return.
